results.title: The Persistance of Memory
results.description: Special Agent Jack Kubrick is given the assignment of finding out what happened to Machine Man after his last public appearence. This includes interviews with people who knew him. He also finds that the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants is also looking for Machine Man, for their own reasons. After finding Machine Man's head, Jack is fatally shot by Mystique.  Still alive, Jack puts the robotic head where his head had been, only to discover that he is Machine Man.

results.title: War Zone Part 1: Road Rage
results.description: The Blood Brothers battle the Road Warriors after the Warriors kill a Blood Brother named Izzy.  The gangwar is broken up by police, but Nemo escapes. He is chased and beaten by Grafik and some of his crew. X-51 intervenes and takes Nemo to his house to recover from the attack. The Warriors, working for Miss Merrick, report to her their failure and are transformed via science into inhuman cyborgs. The Warriors go on a rampage, and X-51 decides to intervene again.

results.title: Fast Lane Part 4: Back on Target
results.description: Spider-Man defeats Mysterio's plot with some aid from the X-Men, The Fantastic Four, the Avengers, and Spider-Girl.

results.title: Space Odyssey
results.description: This issue is text-heavy as it offers a complete retrospective of Machine Man Vol. 1 and X-51, including everyone he's met and adventures that were never shown. At the end, Aaron decides to journey into the Monolith to further his own evolution.

results.title: Against the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants
Ghost in the Shell
results.description: Machine Man takes down the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants. As he does, he discovers he can detect mutants and instantly analyze their abilities and exploit their weaknesses. When he is damaged during the battle, he senses nanotechnology at work inside of him, rebuilding him instantly.  He is the ultimate mutant hunter, a fusion of the Master Mold, Bastion, and himself. During his last appearance before he was deactivated, he copied his essence into an nearby LMD (Life Model Decoy) who later took the name "Jack Kubrick." After defeating the Brotherhood, X-51 flies away to discover more about his new abilities and to rediscover the man in him, Aaron Stack. It is also revealed that Mystique and the Brotherhood were hired by Sebastian Shaw to go after Machine Man, for reasons known only to himself.

results.title: X.E.R.O. Tolerance
results.description: Machine Man (as Aaron Stack) takes some downtime on a Virgina beach, befriending a boy whose father runs a hotel there. Peter Henry Gyrich tracks down X-51 using X.E.R.O. (Xeno-Engramatic Robot Organism), the prototype of the X-model robots. Attacking X-51 on the beach forces Aaron to drop his disguise. He defeats X.E.R.O. and Gyrich, then flies off for parts unknown.

results.title: With Friends Like These
results.description: X-51 goes to his former teammates the Avengers for guidance and support in understanding all the changes he has recently experienced. As he approaches the mansion, he sees Justice and Firestar- 2 young mutants who are also Avengers. His Sentinal-based, mutant-hunting and extermination program goes into effect with devastating results. Jarvis sends out a call to the current Avengers, and the Vision is the first to respond.

results.title: Fast Lane Part 1 of  4: Media Blitz!
results.description: Spider-Man fights with Mysterio and Peter Parker argues with J. Jonah Jameson.

results.title: Circuits Maximus
results.description: X-51 and the Vision battle in Central Park. Leading X-51 back to Avengers Mansion, Vision traps X-51 in cyberspace, where he communicates with Aaron. Teleporting away at the last second, X-51 travels into orbit just above earth. He then converts his body into a satellite, in order to keep his mutant extermination program in check.

results.title: A View To A Kill!
results.description: Sebastian Shaw hires Omoto to go after X-51.  Omoto kidnaps Peter Spaulding --an old associate of X-51's-- to lure X-51 out of his satellite housing. During the battle, X-51's nanites upgrade him again, making him more than a match for the Japanese mercenary.

results.title: Fast Lane Part 2 of 4: Feel the Rush!
results.description: Spider-Man and Mysterio continue to battle on a movie set.

results.title: The Harder They Fall
results.description: Jill and Peter discuss with Aaron the only way to eliminate his Sentinel programming: to erase his hard drive, including all of his memories of his father, his past, and his friends. While Aaron is deciding what to do, the Sentinels attack him. Just as the robots begin to fight, the ante is upped by the appearance of the X-Men.

results.title: Aftermath
results.description: The X-Men and the Sentinels battle, with Machine Man switching sides depending on which of his programs is in control-- his normal program or the Sentinel program. Eventually the Sentinel program takes him over completely. In order to save lives and defeat the Sentinel programs, Machine Man blows himself up.
